texts: Children in the Wini Bruma Kindergarden
Patrocino, Joel, Noel, Bernadete, Jenildo, Narlia, Monica cessy, Berta pinto, Teodoru, Vidal, Lindalva, Odilton
I start my day across the sea.
I stand above the trees, across the sea.
They grow and sometimes become flowers.
There are many trees and flowers thanks to me.
I can also go over the mountains.
I shine on garden where people are.
Fish living in the water also need me.
When the day ends, I go back under the sea, goodbye.
